> This Creamy White Wine Mussel Tagliatelle takes inspiration from classic restaurant dishes to bring a fine dining experience straight into your home! Say hello to a fresh ingredient - mussels! These tiny but delicious shellfish are famous for their pincer-like shells. Dressed in a white wine and garlic reduction, these mussels are worth flexing about!

== Cheesy Garlic Baguette ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the tagliatelle.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(chopped into small pieces). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{4}(grated or pressed).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Place the @demi garlic baguettes{2} onto a lined #medium baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the Cheddar cheese.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and piping hot, ~{12-15%mins}.

== Mussels and Tagliatelle ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in another large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%secs}.

Add the @garlic & white wine Scottish mussels{1%pack} and their liquid into the pan. Stir in the @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Pop the lid on. Cook until piping hot, ~{5%mins}.

Discard any mussels that do not open. IMPORTANT: Ensure the mussels are piping hot throughout.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

When the mussels are cooked, stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @butter{20%g} and half the parsley. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

== Balsamic Dressed Salad ==

When everything's nearly ready, in a large #bowl{}, toss the tomatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%g} with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} until evenly coated.

== Assembly ==

Using a #slotted spoon{}, carefully remove the mussels from the sauce and transfer to a medium bowl. Cover to keep warm.

Stir the tagliatelle and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} into the pan of sauce until well combined. Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed. Add splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the creamy tagliatelle between your bowls. Top with the mussels and remaining parsley.

Serve with the cheesy garlic bread and salad on the side. Enjoy!